		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I found this on Wikipedia earlier, as the complete list of NES games that use the lightgun:
<br />
<br />    * Baby Boomer
<br />    * Barker Bill's Trick Shooting
<br />    * Chiller
<br />    * Duck Hunt
<br />    * Freedom Force
<br />    * Hogan's Alley
<br />    * Gumshoe
<br />    * Gotcha! The Sport!
<br />    * Laser Invasion
<br />    * The Lone Ranger
<br />    * Mechanized Attack
<br />    * Operation Wolf
<br />    * Shooting Range
<br />    * The Adventures of Bayou Billy
<br />    * To The Earth
<br />    * Wild Gunman
<br />
<br />I can't think of any others. Anyone else have any to add?
<br />
<br />The big question is - what about Famicom? Are there any any Famicom gun games that weren't released here in the US or UK? I'd imagine there have to be a few..
<br />
<br />Any help would be appreciated. I look forward to some serious lightgun action on my PowerPak in the near future.
<br />
<br />NC

		

